  "prompt": "Which English songs would you like to listen to again and again without getting bored?",
  "response": "There are many English songs that have a timeless quality and can be enjoyed repeatedly. Here are a few that often resonate well with listeners:\n\n1. **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\" by Queen** - A classic rock opera that offers a blend of genres and unparalleled vocal harmonies.\n2. **\"Imagine\" by John Lennon** - A beautiful, contemplative song about peace and unity.\n3. **\"Hotel California\" by Eagles** - Known for its haunting melody and intricate guitar work, this song tells a captivating story.\n4. **\"Shape of You\" by Ed Sheeran** - A catchy pop tune with an addictive rhythm.\n5. **\"Rolling in the Deep\" by Adele** - Powerful vocals and an emotional backstory make this song unforgettable.\n6. **\"Billie Jean\" by Michael Jackson** - A classic dance track with an iconic beat and lyrics.\n7. **\"Wonderwall\" by Oasis** - A sing-along anthem that evokes nostalgia for many listeners.\n8. **\"Hey Jude\" by The Beatles** - A song that's uplifting and perfect for group singing.\n9. **\"Uptown Funk\" by Mark Ronson ft. Bruno Mars** - A funky, high-energy track that's hard not to dance to.\n10. **\"Someone Like You\" by Adele** - An emotional ballad that connects deeply with listeners.\n\nThese songs encompass a range of genres and themes, making them enjoyable to revisit time and time again.",
